   {:e #blake3 "bfa6eb6ea911897187d03e641416018d557c8d182ded8938228a8e9bc6753173" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: DOGFOOD-4 scored 6.7/10. The invariants concept absorbed 25/29 observations because the domain IS about invariants. Description tuning cannot fix this — the category is legitimately dominant. The fix is hierarchical concept splitting. INSIGHT: The 25 observations in invariants aren't the same. Some are about implementation (fold determinism), some about verification (witness auto-invalidation), some about violation (missing error checks). These are subconcepts that the system already detects (variance=0.95 > SPLIT_THRESHOLD=0.5) but cannot act on. APPROACH: In harvest.rs, after crystallizing uncategorized observations (LIFECYCLE-HARVEST), add a split phase: (1) For each concept with variance > SPLIT_THRESHOLD and member_count >= 6: (2) Load all member observation embeddings (from :exploration/concept Ref + :exploration/embedding). (3) Run crystallize_concepts on just those members with a TIGHTER threshold (JOIN_THRESHOLD * 1.5 — subclusters need to be more similar than the parent). (4) If 2+ subclusters with >= 3 members each emerge: (a) Create child concept entities with hierarchical names: parent_name/subcluster_name (e.g., invariants/verification). (b) Reassign member observations from parent to child (:exploration/concept retargeted). (c) The parent concept remains with updated member_count (reduced). (d) Child concepts get their own centroids, member_counts, total_weights. (5) Report: 'split invariants into invariants/implementation (8 obs) + invariants/verification (6 obs) + invariants/violation (5 obs)'. SCHEMA: :concept/parent (Ref, One) — links child to parent concept. Enables hierarchy traversal. NAME GENERATION: The subcluster naming uses the SAME majority-keyword algorithm (STEER-1b) on the subcluster member texts. The result is prefixed with parent_name/. ACCEPTANCE: (A) A concept with 25 diverse members splits into 2+ subconcepts at harvest. (B) Subconcept names are parent/child format (e.g., invariants/verification). (C) Member counts redistribute correctly (sum of children = original parent). (D) find_nearest_concept matches subconcepts, not just parent. (E) Status shows hierarchical concept inventory. (F) All existing tests pass — splitting is additive, not destructive. DEPENDS-ON: nothing (all infrastructure exists). FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/harvest.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/schema.rs (:concept/parent attr)" :op :assert}
